# Icons and static assets

Full detail lives in-repo—keep rules and files aligned:

- [`docs/asset-naming.md`](docs/asset-naming.md) — kebab-case filenames; spell out product names (not `gtmt`-style abbreviations in shipped names); role suffixes `-logo`, `-mark`, `-icon`, `-og`; semantic folders (e.g. `behind-the-music-tree/`, not source-based names like `cv/`).
- [`docs/logo-assets.md`](docs/logo-assets.md) — prefer **SVG** for scalable marks; **PNG RGBA** when raster is required; extension must match format; dimension and file-size guidance for wordmarks vs square marks vs OG images, plus favicon bundle location under `src/favicons/<project>/`.

## When editing icons/favicons or `package.json`

- After renaming or adding files under `src/icons/`, update **`exports`** and the **`build`** copy step if the folder is new or renamed.
- Keep one favicon bundle per project under `src/favicons/<project-slug>/` and preserve standard filenames (`favicon.svg`, `favicon.ico`, `apple-touch-icon.png`, `icon-192.png`, `icon-512.png` when available).
- If conventions in `docs/*.md` change, update this rule file in the same PR so Cursor stays aligned.

## Examples

- Prefer `grow-the-music-tree-logo.png` over `gtmt.png`.
- Prefer `@behindthemusictree/assets/icons/behind-the-music-tree/audiometa-logo.png` over legacy `icons/cv/...` paths.
